[We are indebted to Richard for kindly agreeing to send us this very brief
summary. He had written to me with some thoughts and I asked him to flesh
them out a bit and send it to us for posting. He has certainly done that.
There is little doubt that "disease" is an exceedingly complex term. Most
of the time we look at the most superficial of its aspects. Richard has
given us an opportunity to delve a little more deeply. Perhaps we will all
begin to consider more than simply who?, what?, when?, where?, and why? and
start thinking in terms of "how?" and then, perhaps, "how not?" - Mod.CHC
